<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>7 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER PS110-7, PS145-7 - REASSEMBLE - INPUT SHAFT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="4">
        <title>INPUT SHAFT</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the snap ring into the input bearing cap (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301652">Figure 52</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301652" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301652" filename="../figg13/g1301652.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 52. Install Snap Ring Into Input Bearing Cap</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Insert the input shaft through the bearing retainer, using an installation sleeve to protect
                the seal (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301653">Figure 53</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301653" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301653" filename="../figg13/g1301653.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 53. Insert Input Shaft Through Bearing Retainer</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Do not use grease on this seal. The shaft and seal must be oil-free when mated to provide an
                        effective seal.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Expand the snap ring through the provided slot while pressing the input shaft assembly into
                the bearing retainer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301654">Figure 54</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301654" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301654" filename="../figg13/g1301654.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 54. Expand Snap Ring Through Slot</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">When snap ring grooves on the input shaft bearing and bearing cap are in proper alignment,
                discontinue pressing. Seat the snap ring in place. Inspect the assembly to assure the snap ring is
                properly seated and secured (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301655">Figure 55</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301655" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301655" filename="../figg13/g1301655.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 55. Seat Snap Ring in Place</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
